linearInterpolation.model.interpolation

Class Interpolation

  • java.lang.Object
    • linearInterpolation.model.interpolation.Interpolation
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    LinearInterpolation

    public abstract class Interpolation
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    Interpolation is a class used for interpolation calculations. Calculations are executed in two steps. The first step is setting initial x and y values by call initialize method. The second step is calling calculateFunctionValue method, which returns y value for given x value.

    The class must be extended to specify, which function must be represented.
